Background
In ORMS, each control is linked to a regulation that specifies the relevant business area.

Transformation Rules
Control Instances:

For each control, create an instance for every unique combination of segment, line of business, country, and theme found in the associated ERIC regulation.
Since a single ERIC regulation can include multiple lines of business, multiple instances may be generated from a single regulation.
Avoiding Duplicates:

If the same line of business appears in different ERIC regulations for the same control, do not create duplicate instances.
Example:
Regulation 1: "Capital Markets" (Segment), "Conflicts of Interest" (Theme), "Canada" (Country), "Global Research" (Line of Business).
Regulation 2: Same segment, theme, and country, but with two lines of business: "Global Research" and "Corporate Finance."
Result: Only two instances are created, one for each unique line of business.
If duplicate instances are avoided, the ERIC Regulation IDs will be combined in a single instance, separated by a comma (,).
Other Data Transformations:

Lines of Defence: Both "2LOD" and "2LOD - CoG" in ORMS will be treated as "2LOD."
